  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The work is further based on a point cloud autoencoder proposed by Achlioptas et al. (2018), that is further advanced in (Rios et al. 2019a, b).",
    "The PC-VAE architecture consists of five 1D convolutional layers (as described in (Qi et al. 2017a)), with ReLU after each layer (Nair and Hinton 2010), and at the end a batch normalization layer (Saha et al. 2019).",
    "The decoder part consists of three fully connected layers.",
    "Although this approach has a huge potential, further optimization is needed to create a complete cooperative framework.",
    "Yang et al. (2019a) tackle the problem of generating realistic 3D point clouds by encoding them as the distributions of shapes, which in turn are the distributions of points."
